text.tspan: Thank you for reaching out to us regarding the issue you are experiencing with your coffee machine not powering up. I understand how frustrating this can be, and I'm here to assist you.

After reviewing our knowledge base, I found some relevant information that may help you troubleshoot the issue. In the document titled "How to Update the Firmware on the Contoso SmartBrew 3000 Coffee Machine" , there are

steps provided to update the firmware of your coffee machine. Although this document does not specifically address the issue of the machine not powering up, updating the firmware can sometimes resolve such issues by improving
the performance and functionality of the device.

To update the firmware on your coffee machine, please follow the steps outlined in the document . Make sure to check for available firmware updates on our website or contact our customer support team for assistance. It is

important to download the latest firmware update file and save it to your computer. Then, prepare a USB drive with at least 1 GB of available storage space and format it to the FAT32 file system. Copy the firmware update file to the

root directory of the USB drive and insert it into the coffee machine's USB port. Follow the on-screen instructions to confirm the firmware update and wait for the update process to complete. After the coffee machine has restarted,
verify that the firmware has been updated to the latest version.

If updating the firmware does not resolve the issue, I recommend contacting our customer support team for further assistance. They have the expertise to guide you through additional troubleshooting steps or provide further
instructions based on your specific situation.

I hope this information helps in resolving the issue with your coffee machine not powering up. If you have any further questions or need additional assistance, please don't hesitate to reach out to me.
